parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or become stuck in a gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle jerks or vibrates
the transmission overheats
the vehicle cannot accelerate
the vehicle stalls or loses power when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission cooling system can cause the transmission to overheat, leading to premature wear and failure, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission overheats
the vehicle loses power
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the transmission overheats
the vehicle cannot accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive shaft can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The drive shaft breaks
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard flashes or remains illuminated
indicating a malfunction in the airbag system; the passenger airbag may not deploy in an accident; the driver's airbag may not deploy in an accident; the airbag sensor may malfunction
causing the airbag to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag sensor can cause the passenger airbag to malfunction, leading to the non-deployment of the airbag in an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard flashes or remains illuminated
indicating a malfunction in the passenger airbag sensor; the passenger airbag may not deploy in an accident; the passenger airbag sensor may malfunction
causing the airbag to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the non-deployment of airbags in an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard flashes or remains illuminated
indicating a malfunction in the clock spring; the airbag system may malfunction
causing the airbag to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of acceleration can cause the vehicle to slow down or stall, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when merging onto highways or climbing steep inclines.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate when pressing the gas pedal
even when the pedal is pressed to the floor. The RPMs may increase
but the vehicle does not move forward or accelerates slowly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to accelerate, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage
causing the vehicle to lose power or stall. The vehicle may also experience unusual noises
such as whining or grinding sounds
when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control malfunction can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to maintain the set speed
causing the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly. The vehicle may also experience sudden loss of power or acceleration.
